summary: Just played Pokemon Coral, a romhack of Pokemon Gold/Silver/Crystal which aims to recreate the feeling of Gen II games, so that...
caption: Just played Pokemon Coral, a romhack of Pokemon Gold/Silver/Crystal which aims to recreate the feeling of Gen II games, so that naturally intrigued me since that’s probably my most nostalgic generation. As you can tell, there are a lot more Pokemon available than just from the first two generations, so that made deciding on a team difficult with each new route you explored. I tried to stick with their GSC palette but in the end I cheated a bit to create a better lighting.
